So I went outside and I was calling for my cat,
所以我跑出去喊我的猫，

374
00:13:20,340 --> 00:13:22,260
and I was like, Mr. Finn, where are you?
我说，芬恩先生，你在哪里？

375
00:13:22,260 --> 00:13:23,340
How did you know he fell out?
你怎么知道它掉下去了？

376
00:13:23,340 --> 00:13:24,140
I just knew.
我就是知道。

377
00:13:24,140 --> 00:13:24,540
Yeah?
是吗？

378
00:13:24,540 --> 00:13:24,900
Yeah.
嗯。

379
00:13:24,900 --> 00:13:25,700
Mother's instinct.
母亲的直觉。

380
00:13:25,700 --> 00:13:27,020
I guess so.
我想是吧。

381
00:13:27,020 --> 00:13:30,660
So he was calling back to me, and so I picked him up
它回应了我，所以我把它抱起来

382
00:13:30,660 --> 00:13:31,860
and brought him to the house,
带回了家，

383
00:13:31,860 --> 00:13:33,700
and we had to bring him to the vet,
我们不得不带它去看兽医，

384
00:13:33,700 --> 00:13:36,180
and it was 2.30, 3 in the morning at this time,
那时是凌晨两点半、三点，

385
00:13:36,180 --> 00:13:40,860
and the vet was not very happy that we woke him up out of bed.
兽医被我们从床上叫起来很不高兴。

386
00:13:40,860 --> 00:13:42,820
But that was a really good emergency, though.
但那确实是紧急情况。

387
00:13:42,820 --> 00:13:43,540
Yeah.
是啊。

388
00:13:43,540 --> 00:13:45,820
So anyway, we brought him to the vet.
总之，我们带它去了兽医那里。

389
00:13:45,820 --> 00:13:48,940
He was in critical condition for a couple of days,
它情况危急了好几天，

390
00:13:48,940 --> 00:13:53,820
and then we had to keep him in the vet's ICU for about a week.
然后我们不得不把它留在兽医的ICU大约一周。

391
00:13:53,820 --> 00:13:55,020
He broke his back.
它摔断了背。

392
00:13:55,020 --> 00:13:57,620
He broke two of his legs.
它摔断了两条腿。

393
00:13:57,620 --> 00:13:58,420
Wow.
哇。

394
00:13:58,420 --> 00:14:01,020
Yeah, and so he was in the hospital for three weeks
是啊，所以它在医院住了三周

395
00:14:01,020 --> 00:14:04,620
and then at home on bed rest for another three weeks.
然后在家卧床休息又三周。

396
00:14:04,620 --> 00:14:06,540
But now he's good as new.
但现在它完好如初了。

397
00:14:06,540 --> 00:14:07,260
Good as new.
完好如初。

398
00:14:07,260 --> 00:14:07,740
Yeah.
是啊。

399
00:14:07,740 --> 00:14:10,300
He used up one of his seven lives.
它用掉了九条命中的一条。

400
00:14:10,300 --> 00:14:10,780
Nine lives.
九条命。

401
00:14:10,780 --> 00:14:11,180
Nine?
九条命？

402
00:14:11,180 --> 00:14:11,540
Nine.
九条命。

403
00:14:11,540 --> 00:14:12,340
Yeah.
是啊。

404
00:14:12,340 --> 00:14:14,300
I think maybe eight of his nine lives.
我觉得他可能用掉了八条命。

405
00:14:14,300 --> 00:14:15,460
He's only got one left.
他只剩一条命了。

406
00:14:15,460 --> 00:14:15,980
Yeah.
是啊。

407
00:14:15,980 --> 00:14:17,380
Wow, that's an interesting story.
哇，这故事真有意思。

408
00:14:17,380 --> 00:14:20,300
I guess that's the inspiration under this dialogue.
我想这就是这段对话的灵感来源。

409
00:14:20,300 --> 00:14:21,180
Exactly.
没错。

410
00:14:21,180 --> 00:14:24,980
Sometimes we Anglos really treat our cats
有时候我们西方人真的把猫

411
00:14:24,980 --> 00:14:27,380
and our hamsters and our dogs like they're our children.
还有仓鼠和狗当成自己的孩子。

412
00:14:27,380 --> 00:14:28,100
Yeah, yeah.
是啊，是啊。

413
00:14:28,100 --> 00:14:29,220
No, that's good.
不，这挺好的。

414
00:14:29,220 --> 00:14:31,340
Well, I'm glad Mr. Finn is OK and he's
嗯，我很高兴芬恩先生没事了，他

415
00:14:31,340 --> 00:14:32,540
walking and good as new.
又能走路了，跟新的一样。

416
00:14:32,540 --> 00:14:33,500
Yep, good as new.
对，跟新的一样。

417
00:14:33,500 --> 00:14:37,940
So maybe our users have some stories about their pets
所以也许我们的用户有一些关于宠物

418
00:14:37,940 --> 00:14:39,340
being taken to the hospital.
被送进医院的故事。

419
00:14:39,340 --> 00:14:40,140
I want to hear.
我想听听。

420
00:14:40,140 --> 00:14:41,500
Yeah, that should be interesting.
是啊，那应该挺有意思的。

421
00:14:41,500 --> 00:14:44,260
I've never had a pet actually break a leg or anything,
我从来没有宠物摔断腿之类的经历，

422
00:14:44,260 --> 00:14:46,500
